      "content": "It's a myth that wine enhances diazepam's effect; in fact, it's a recipe for unpredictable drowsiness. Even a small glass can amplify the sedative effects, pushing you into a dangerous level of impairment. If you want to sleep, take your prescribed dose alone and focus on your breathing. If you're feeling restless, you need to check with your actual doctor, not rely on these common myths.",
